{
  "name": "Solar System (Sun to Oort Cloud)",
  "description": "Simplified radial cross-section from the Sun through the solar system to the Oort Cloud. Hydrogen-helium stellar core, rocky inner planets (silicate proxy), gas giant region (hydrogen-methane), the Kuiper Belt ice region, and the vast Oort Cloud of icy-rocky debris. Layer thicknesses are proportional to order-of-magnitude scale, not to true AU distances. Demonstrates the dramatic density gradient from stellar plasma (~1400 kg/m³) to near-perfect vacuum (~10⁻²⁵ kg/m³).",
